article.headline: Cross scores 19 to propel Massachusetts past Saint Louis 84-73
article.description: — Matt Cross had 19 points in Massachusetts' 84-73 win over Saint Louis on Saturday night.
article.linkText: Cross scores 19 to propel Massachusetts past Saint Louis 84-73
article.story: ST. LOUIS -- — Matt Cross had 19 points in Massachusetts' 84-73 win over Saint Louis on Saturday night. Cross added five rebounds and five assists for the Minutemen (13-7, 4-4 Atlantic 10 Conference). Rahsool Diggins added 15 points while shooting 5 for 10 (2 for 6 from 3-point range) and 3 of 5 from the free throw line, and they also had six rebounds. Keon Thompson was 4 of 13 shooting, including 2 for 4 from 3-point range, and went 4 for 4 from the line to finish with 14 points. The Billikens (8-12, 1-6) were led in scoring by Gibson Jimerson, who finished with 16 points and four assists. Larry Hughes Jr. added 14 points for Saint Louis. Bradley Ezewiro also had 12 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
